{
  "doc_id": "42163",
  "text": "All stages of phagolysosome formation involve dynamic interactions with vesicles of the endosomal system. During particle engulfment, endosomes fuse with the phagosomal cup, providing membranes required for particle envelopment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . At later stages, early endosomes, late endosomes, and lysosomes sequentially fuse with phagosomes to deliver proteins needed for degradation of luminal material [CITATION_4] .",
